\mathbf{x}(t) = \frac12t^2 \mathbf{a} + \mathbf{u} t + \mathbf{d}
t^2 \in [0,\infty)
\mathbf{a}, \mathbf{u}, \mathbf{d}
 \frac{d}{dt}\begin{bmatrix}{1 \\2}\end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix}{\frac{d}{dt}1 \\\frac{d}{dt}2}\end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix}{0 \\0}\end{bmatrix}
 \frac{d}{dt}t^2\begin{bmatrix}{1 \\2}\end{bmatrix} = \frac{d}{dt}\begin{bmatrix}{t^2 \\2t^2}\end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix}{\frac{d}{dt}t^2 \\\frac{d}{dt}2t^2}\end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix}{2t \\4t}\end{bmatrix} = 2t\begin{bmatrix}{1 \\2}\end{bmatrix}
t^2
